result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan K. Murray #00529728 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Receiving or Concealing Stolen Property (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Ryan K. Murray #00529728 in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Defendant Ryan K. Murray #00529728 in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states what the hearing is about today.  Atty Hendee states that an American Family rep would be able to be called if need be.  Atty Zamzow states that her client is arguing his ability to pay.  
Court gets victim American Famil on the phone.  American Family rep states that he does not need to participate in today's hearing.
Court finds that American Family has been notified of the hearing and will allow them to not participate in the hearing today.

Atty Zamzow states that her client is in custody and will be until August 2020 and therefore, does not have the ability to pay.
Atty Hendee makes arguments and asks the court to order the restitution as is; joint and several with Bronson Bantleon 15CF6.

BY THE COURT:   Court finds the defendant responsible for full amount of Restitution including surcharges as submitted; joint and several as stated in the supplement.

Defendant Ryan K. Murray in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Defendant Ryan K. Murray in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee moves to amend Ct. 1 to 943.34(1)(a), Receiving Stolen Property.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement to the amended Ct. 1 with an argued sentence.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed and read-in.  Atty Hendee states that the parties are stipulating to Restitution as in the supplement, Joint and Several,  however, the defendant is requesting a Restitution Hearing for American Family.  Atty Zamzow agrees.
BY THE COURT:  Court amends Ct. 1 to 943.34(1)(a).
Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty to the amended Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed and read-in.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations; defendant is currently in the Wisconsin State Prison System.
Atty Zamzow makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Amended Ct. 1:  Court orders 9 months in the Marquette County Jail; consecutive to any other sentence
Court Costs = $243.00
Restitution; joint and several as listed in the supplement
Credit = 0 days
Defendant is eligable for Challange Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program
Ct. 2:  Dismissed and read-in

Restitution Hearing to be set for the remainder of the Restitution for American Family Insurance.  Restitution hearing scheduled for February 4, 2016 at 10:30 am.
